<paragraph blockId="248.[136,778,1669,2070]" lastBlockId="249.[136,778,173,811]" lastPageId="249" lastPageNumber="250" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">
In his visit to BSKU in 2009, T. Iwamoto (CAS) informed the present author that 
<taxonomicName box="[497,650,1942,1968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="248" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kamoharai">
<emphasis box="[497,650,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">N. kamoharai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also shares many features with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gilbert, 1905)" baseAuthorityName="Gilbert" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[368,696,1975,2002]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="248" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obliquata">
<emphasis box="[368,511,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">N. obliquata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gilbert, C. H." box="[530,687,1975,2002]" pageId="248" pageNumber="249" pagination="573 - 713" refId="ref285669" refString="Gilbert, C. H. (1905) The deep-sea fishes of the Hawaiian Islands. In: Jordan, D. S. &amp; Evermann, B. W. (Eds.), The Aquatic Resources of the Hawaiian Islands. Bulletin of the U. S. Fish Commission, 23. Government Printing Office, Washington DC, pp. 573 - 713, figs. 230 - 276, pls. 66 - 101. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 12624" type="book chapter" year="1905">Gilbert, 1905</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, a rare species confined to the Hawaiian-Emperor Seamount Chain. The latter species was originally described from a small juvenile collected from 
<collectingRegion box="[1182,1263,1669,1695]" country="United States of America" name="Hawaii" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">Hawaii</collectingRegion>
[USNM 51514, 
<typeStatus box="[810,908,1703,1729]" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">holotype</typeStatus>
(ca. 
<quantity box="[972,1056,1704,1730]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="248" pageNumber="249" unit="mm" value="24.0">24 mm</quantity>
HL, 127+ mm TL, fide 
<bibRefCitation author="Sazonov, Y. I." pageId="248" pageNumber="249" pagination="149 - 160" refId="ref298922" refString="Sazonov, Y. I. (1994) Additions to the list of macrourids (Gadiformes, Bathygadidae, and Macrouridae) from the Northwest Pacific Ridge. Journal of Ichthyology, 34, 98 - 115. [Originally published in Russian in Voprosy Ikhtiologii, 34, 149 - 160.]" type="journal article" year="1994">Sazonov 1994:103</bibRefCitation>
)], and is poorly represented in museum collections. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sazonov, Y. I." box="[959,1151,1772,1798]" pageId="248" pageNumber="249" pagination="149 - 160" refId="ref298922" refString="Sazonov, Y. I. (1994) Additions to the list of macrourids (Gadiformes, Bathygadidae, and Macrouridae) from the Northwest Pacific Ridge. Journal of Ichthyology, 34, 98 - 115. [Originally published in Russian in Voprosy Ikhtiologii, 34, 149 - 160.]" type="journal article" year="1994">Sazonov (1994)</bibRefCitation>
recorded an additional specimen of this species from Ojin Guyot in the Emperor Seamounts (ZMMGU P.18245, 
<quantity box="[1175,1277,1839,1866]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.06" pageId="248" pageNumber="249" unit="mm" value="60.6">60.6 mm</quantity>
HL, 398+ mm TL), although he considered his identification tentative due to a number of differences related to the difference in body size between the 
<typeStatus box="[1062,1160,1942,1968]" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">holotype</typeStatus>
and the second specimen. An examination of Sazonov’s (1994) specimen revealed its close similarity with 
<taxonomicName box="[1090,1247,2010,2036]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="248" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kamoharai">
<emphasis box="[1090,1247,2010,2036]" italics="true" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">N. kamoharai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the 
<typeStatus box="[1353,1451,2010,2036]" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[845,1004,2044,2070]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="248" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kamoharai">
<emphasis box="[845,1004,2044,2070]" italics="true" pageId="248" pageNumber="249">N. kamoharai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from that specimen in having shorter barbel (12% HL vs. 17%), pelvic fin (44% HL vs. 65%), and pectoral fin (50% HL vs. 59%). Spinulation of the body scales is also different between the two specimens. In the 
<typeStatus box="[345,443,275,301]" pageId="249" pageNumber="250">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[484,640,275,301]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="249" pageNumber="250" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kamoharai">
<emphasis box="[484,640,275,301]" italics="true" pageId="249" pageNumber="250">N. kamoharai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the middle row of spinules is distinctly larger than adjacent rows (
<figureCitation box="[144,243,343,370]" captionStart="FIGURE 167" captionStartId="248.[136,235,1535,1559]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,989,1499]" captionTargetId="figure-264@248.[151,1436,989,1499]" captionTargetPageId="248" captionText="FIGURE 167. Scanning electron micrographs showing body scale (from the dorsum below the interdorsal space) of Nezumia kamoharai. BSKU 14202, holotype, 62.4 mm HL. (A) View from above; (B) oblique view. [Photos: NSMT]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6423146" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6423146/files/figure.png" pageId="249" pageNumber="250">Fig. 167</figureCitation>
), whereas in the “ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gilbert" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[448,589,343,369]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="249" pageNumber="250" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obliquata">
<emphasis box="[448,589,343,369]" italics="true" pageId="249" pageNumber="250">N. obliquata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” specimen from the Emperor Seamounts, the middle row is not especially enlarged (
<bibRefCitation author="Sazonov, Y. I." box="[251,421,411,437]" pageId="249" pageNumber="250" pagination="149 - 160" refId="ref298922" refString="Sazonov, Y. I. (1994) Additions to the list of macrourids (Gadiformes, Bathygadidae, and Macrouridae) from the Northwest Pacific Ridge. Journal of Ichthyology, 34, 98 - 115. [Originally published in Russian in Voprosy Ikhtiologii, 34, 149 - 160.]" type="journal article" year="1994">Sazonov 1994</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 3). These two specimens are almost equal in size, and their differences appear to warrant specific separation. The status of Sazonov’s (1994) specimen is still uncertain, but it does not seem to represent either 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gilbert" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[347,487,547,573]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="249" pageNumber="250" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obliquata">
<emphasis box="[347,487,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="249" pageNumber="250">N. obliquata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nor 
<taxonomicName box="[540,694,547,573]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="249" pageNumber="250" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kamoharai">
<emphasis box="[540,694,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="249" pageNumber="250">N. kamoharai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on the original description given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gilbert, C. H." box="[562,728,581,608]" pageId="249" pageNumber="250" pagination="573 - 713" refId="ref285669" refString="Gilbert, C. H. (1905) The deep-sea fishes of the Hawaiian Islands. In: Jordan, D. S. &amp; Evermann, B. W. (Eds.), The Aquatic Resources of the Hawaiian Islands. Bulletin of the U. S. Fish Commission, 23. Government Printing Office, Washington DC, pp. 573 - 713, figs. 230 - 276, pls. 66 - 101. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 12624" type="book chapter" year="1905">Gilbert (1905)</bibRefCitation>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[136,234,615,641]" pageId="249" pageNumber="250">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gilbert" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[280,424,615,641]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="249" pageNumber="250" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obliquata">
<emphasis box="[280,424,615,641]" italics="true" pageId="249" pageNumber="250">N. obliquata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[586,744,615,641]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Macrouridae" genus="Nezumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gadiformes" pageId="249" pageNumber="250" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kamoharai">
<emphasis box="[586,744,615,641]" italics="true" pageId="249" pageNumber="250">N. kamoharai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having fewer pelvic-fin rays (12 vs. 13) and smaller body scales (9 below the second dorsal-fin origin vs. 7.5). To resolve the taxonomic status of these species, a further study should be done when more specimens become available.
</paragraph>
